<TITLE> Ex-Ittefaq journalist sues Mainul, wife for libel </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 7 (bdnews24.com)A senior reporter of The Day Ittefaq has filed a defamation suit against Moinul Hosein , executive director-1 of Ittefaq Group of Publication and his wife, Saju Hossain, publisher of The Daily Ittefaq, for . Faraji Ajmal Hossain filed the case with Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court at 10 am Thursday. Magistrate Konika Biswas did not give any order until 3pm other than recording the statement of the plaintiff. The case statement said that Faraji had been working for the daily with much reputation since his appointment back in 1975. But after his appointment as adviser to the caretaker government, Moinul Husein started filing false cases against his brother Anwar Hossain Monju who was forced out of the country in a bid to wrest control of the daily. As the plaintiff was on good terms with Monju, Moinul and Saju subjected him to frequent harassment and ultimately terminated him on Apri29, 2009 without giving him the chance to defend himself. Faraji also said in the case statement that his termination from the job had lowered his honour and dignity in the eye of society. b
